  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 375°F (190°C).",
    "In a large bowl, whisk together the almond flour, coconut sugar, salt, black pepper, and Tunisian spice blend.",
    "Add the prasadham ghee and mix until the mixture resembles coarse crumbs.",
    "Stir in the chopped glace cherry, sun-dried tomatoes, kalamata olives, and chopped fresh parsley.",
    "In a separate bowl, whisk together the eggs and crumbled feta cheese.",
    "Pour the egg mixture over the dry ingredients and stir until just combined.",
    "Transfer the mixture to a 9x13 inch baking dish and top with the shio-koji-cured eggplant.",
    "Bake for 35 minutes or until the edges are golden brown and the center is set.",
    "Let the bake cool for 10 minutes before slicing and serving."
  ],
